        <h4 class=" grey-text">International Business Development</h4>
        <blockquote>The only way to get through adversity is by finding values that are important in life; rediscovering a sense of belonging to a project a community; embracing and sharing positiveness; looking ahead; and taking your destiny into your own hands; and do your best no matter what...</blockquote>
        <p>Paul-Henri Duillet has an extensive international experience within the Cosmetic and Luxury industry, having worked for L’Oréal and LVMH, 2 leaders in their own category.</p>
        <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="team-read-more pink-text" >Read More</a>
        <div class="team-more-bio" >
            <p>Throughout the last 25 years, Paul-Henri has developed very specific skills in successfully turning-around and managing fast growing Business Units, opening markets (Asia, Russia), designing global marketing strategies (Luxury, Consumers Goods) and adapting them locally efficiently. Despite adverse environments, he has lead commercial teams (Department Stores, Perfumeries, Food Retailers) delivering double-digit growth. As a genuine team builder, he has created and guided successful multi-cultural teams.</p>
            <p>From 2006 to 2010, Paul-Henri Duillet, was General Manager of Parfums Christian Dior in Russia, subsidiary of the LVMH Group. He lead his newly constituted team to make Dior Russia the world most profitable subsidiary and market leader in 2 years. In 2010, they achieved to put back Dior to its pre-crisis level (2009).</p>
            <p>Prior to joining LVMH, Paul-Henri handled various ‘hands-on’ roles within the L’Oréal Group: Country Manager in the Philippines, Managing Director of the Malaysian subsidiary, Deputy-Zone Manager taking care of consumer goods in Asia, International Marketing Manager for Asia, Middle East, Africa and the Pacific Rim. The challenge was to generate growth and value, selecting the winning products and entering the right markets in the most cost effective way. </p>
            <p>Paul-Henri was born in Paris, France, to a British mother and a French father. He naturally went to the Lycée International (St Germain) to obtain a bilingual education: French and International Baccalaureate. Consequently, he graduated from leading Business school ESSEC (MBA) and the Paris-Dauphine University (pre-doctorate). Paul-Henri has lived in Sri Lanka, Venezuela, Malaysia, the Philippines and Russia. He is fluent in French, English, Spanish and speaks Russian.</p>
