        <p>An accomplished executive in the private, non-profit, and academic sectors, Eric Sinoway is a recognized authority in the areas of partnership development, fundraising, non-profit strategy, and entrepreneurship. He is a well-regarded organizational strategist and a captivating speaker who has been featured at Columbia, Cornell, NYU, Harvard, and a wide variety of industry events and trade shows.</p>
        <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="team-read-more pink-text" >Read More</a>
        <div class="team-more-bio" >
            <p>Throughout his career, Eric has worked with some of the world’s leading organizations and most accomplished individuals. He reinvented and led the successful and widely emulated corporate-sponsorship program at Cendant Corporation, a Fortune 500 company. While working at Joie de Vivre Hotels, he helped conceive a highly regarded hospitality development that earned features in USA Today and The Wall Street Journal.</p>
            <p>Before co-founding Axcess Worldwide with his long-time business partner Kirk Posmantur, Eric was a senior development officer at Harvard University, where he was a catalyst for a series of large, complex philanthropic gifts from individuals, governments, and organizations worldwide. These accomplishments at Harvard built on experience with the Todd Wagner Foundation and Arnold Schwarzenegger’s After-School All-Stars, where Eric helped conceive and lead a national after-school technology initiative called MIRACLES.
            <p>Eric is a partner in Double Cross Vodka, a top-shelf spirit produced in the Slovak Republic; Patagonia Sur, an innovative for-profit conservation project in Patagonia, Chile; and Radical Skincare, the world’s most powerful anti-oxidant skin care. Eric is the author of Howard’s Gift: Uncommon Wisdom to Inspire Your Life’s Work, a book written in cooperation with iconic Harvard Business School professor, Howard H. Stevenson, that St. Martin’s Press is releasing on October 2nd.</p>
            <p>Eric earned his undergraduate degree at Cornell University’s School of Hotel Administration and received his master’s degree at Harvard’s Kennedy School.</p>
